Merrill Lynch says yet to choose Matav IPO listing . Merrill Lynch said on Thursday that Hungarian telecommunications company Matav ' s possible international public offering would be very attractive , but it was unable to specify where the company would seek a listing . " It will be a very attractive offering , regardless of where it is listed , " Doug Rediker , Merrill Lynch ' s director for central and east European Banking told Reuters . Matav said on Thursday it had chosen Merrill Lynch as financial adviser and global coordinator for a potential issue . 
